pr_review_comment_body:
If you're creating an object you don't need to put quotes around the properties

i.e. you could just do `{baseResult: baseResult, ... }`

Also, you can avoid a bit of duplication by making the if clause just initialize the array if it doesn't exist, then pushing unconditionally:

```js
if (!$scope.compareResults[baseTestName]) {
   $scope.compareResults[baseTestName] = [];
}
$scope.compareResults[baseTestName].push({baseResult: baseResult, ...});
```

curious, why there is a dup above
```
_registerOptimizer<FuseConsecutiveTransposes>();
_registerOptimizer<FuseConsecutiveTransposes>();
```
any specific reason?
